-- Peru Tax Collection Rose 3.9% Last Month, Andina Reports
-- B y   J o h n   Q u i g l e y
-- 2012-07-05T19:44:06Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-05/peru-tax-collection-rose-3-9-last-month-andina-reports.html
Peru’s  tax collection  rose 3.9
percent to 6.17 billion soles ($2.3 billion) last month from the
same month a year earlier, Andina  reported .  Sales tax collection fell 1.1 percent as import growth
eased, the state news agency said citing data from the
government’s tax and import duty collection agency.  To contact the reporter on this story:
John Quigley in Lima at 
